name: Lucia at the Jaboticaba Tree
description:
))) SOUND ON (((

Sweet itanhangá grapes,
tell me your secrets.

What do we know about our ancestrals?
Take him your arms,
baby Arakere, son of Lúcia, 
The face of a humanity that never came to be.

What if in the past, 
a baby Australopithecus,
developed a new form of inteligence,
a sweet way of interacting with the surroundings.

If I could travel in time where would I go?
